CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 11, 1958, pg. A10, reads: "AKAs Entertain Supreme Basileus - Members of the Iota Chapter of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Pittsburgh's graduate chapter, entertained Supreme Basileus Arnette G. Wallace, third from right, at a banquet held in Schenley Room of Pittsburgh's Student Union Building (the former Hotel Schenley). Mrs. Wallace spoke at the Carver Day luncheon Saturday at Gateway Plaza.  Left to right: Mrs. Nan Currington, Miss Lee Bertha West, Mrs. Jessie M. Vann, Mrs. Wallace, Mrs. LaRue Frederick and Miss Stephanie Jonson, Iota Chapter Basileus. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left: Nan Moone Currington, Elizabeth McCombs or Lee Bertha West, Jessie Vann, Arnette B. Wallace, LaRue Frederick, and Stephanie Jonson gathered in front of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority banner, in University of Pittsburgh Student Union
